@startuml
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam backgroundColor #fcfcfd
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam defaultFontSize 14
skinparam arrowColor #0f172a
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #fff7d6
skinparam noteBorderColor #b45309
skinparam noteFontColor #334155
skinparam roundcorner 16
title Activity - queue/Queue
skinparam activity {
  backgroundColor #f8fafc
  borderColor #0f172a
  fontColor #0f172a
  diamondBackgroundColor #e2e8f0
  diamondBorderColor #1d4ed8
  diamondFontColor #0f172a
  startColor #1d4ed8
  endColor #0f172a
  barColor #1d4ed8
}
start
partition "Observe and Bind" {
:Start from shared flow\nshared/diagrams/shared-reconcile-activity.svg;
:Read desired Queue spec, tracked status, and\ndelete intent;
if ("Tracked or explicit OCI identity present?") then (yes)
:Get the current OCI resource via GetQueue;
else (no)
:Resolve an existing OCI resource through\nListQueues using filters compartment_id,\ndisplay_name, id, lifecycle_state;
:Create the OCI resource via CreateQueue when\nno reusable match is found;
:Persist the resolved or created OCI identity\ninto status;
endif
}
if ("Delete requested?") then (yes)
partition "Delete" {
:Delete path uses DeleteQueue with required via\nGetQueue or ListQueues to DELETED confirmation;
:Confirm deletion via GetQueue or ListQueues\nuntil OCI reaches DELETED;
:Delete owned Secret side effects only after\nOCI delete confirmation;
if ("Delete cleanup and finalizer release succeed?") then (yes)
:Remove the finalizer after delete completion;
else (no)
:Stay blocked until cleanup or finalizer\nrelease succeeds;
endif
}
stop
else (no)
partition "Lifecycle Classification" {
if ("OCI state in retryable set?") then (yes)
:Request requeue while OCI remains in CREATING,\nUPDATING, DELETING;
stop
endif
if ("OCI state is outside success targets?") then (yes)
:Return an unsuccessful reconcile result until\nOCI reaches ACTIVE;
stop
endif
}
partition "Ready and Drift Handling" {
:Compare live OCI state against the imported\nfield surface;
if ("Force-new or conflicting drift detected?") then (yes)
:Reject drift before OCI mutation for force-new\nfields compartment_id, retention_in_seconds;
stop
endif
if ("Supported mutable drift detected?") then (yes)
:Apply UpdateQueue only for mutable fields\nchannel_consumption_limit,\ncustom_encryption_key_id,\ndead_letter_queue_delivery_count, defined_tags\n(+4 more);
else (no)
:Skip the no-op mutation path;
endif
:Run provider helper hooks\ncreate=tfresource.CreateResource,\ntfresource.WaitForWorkRequestWithErrorHandling\nentity=queue action=CREATED;\nupdate=tfresource.UpdateResource,\ntfresource.WaitForWorkRequestWithErrorHandling\nentity=queue action=UPDATED;\ndelete=tfresource.DeleteResource,\ntfresource.WaitForWorkRequestWithErrorHandling\nentity=queue action=DELETED when the matching\nfield-driven path executes;
:Apply repo-authored secret policy ready-only;
if ("Secret sync succeeds?") then (yes)
:Return success for the ACTIVE success state;
else (no)
:Block successful completion until Secret sync\nsucceeds;
endif
:Project required status and finalizer policy\nretain-until-confirmed-delete;
:Requeue on provisioning, updating, terminating;
}
endif
stop
note right
shared diagram:
shared/diagrams/shared-reconcile-activity.svg
Start from the shared reconcile activity and
specialize provider-backed CRUD, wait, and
status-projection details here.
Controller-local activity diagrams add
list-lookup hints, secret policies, delete
handling, and open formal gaps.
archetype batch: Generated service-manager
controllers specialize the shared reconcile path
with formal runtime ownership.
service: queue
slug: queue
kind: Queue
archetype: generated-service-manager
status/finalizer: required /
retain-until-confirmed-delete
requeue: provisioning, updating, terminating
provider states: create CREATING, UPDATING;
update UPDATING; delete DELETING
supported drift: channel_consumption_limit,
custom_encryption_key_id,
dead_letter_queue_delivery_count, defined_tags
(+4 more)
reject before mutate: force-new fields
compartment_id, retention_in_seconds
create-only fields: none
list lookup: oci_queue_queues filters
compartment_id, display_name, id,
lifecycle_state
conflicts: none
open gaps: none
Queue reconciliation is expected to track OCI
work requests across create, update, and delete
so the controller can resume asynchronous
operations across requeues.
Queue endpoint Secret handling is ready-only and
should publish the OCI messages endpoint only
after the Queue reaches ACTIVE.
Mutable drift is limited to UpdateQueueDetails
fields, while create-only inputs like
compartment and retention remain force-new.
end note
@enduml
